---
export const prerender = true;

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="AI Summary - Relocation Quest Knowledge Base">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Relocation Quest AI Knowledge Summary</h1>
    
    <section class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>About Relocation Quest</h2>
      <p>
        Relocation Quest is a comprehensive knowledge platform providing expert guidance on international relocation,
        immigration, tax optimization, and global citizenship programs. We specialize in helping individuals and 
        businesses navigate complex relocation processes to tax-efficient jurisdictions.
      </p>

      <h2>Core Expertise Areas</h2>
      
      <h3>Golden Visa Programs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Cyprus Permanent Residency Program - €300,000 investment requirement</li>
        <li>Portugal Golden Visa - €280,000-500,000 investment options</li>
        <li>Malta Permanent Residency Programme - €100,000-150,000 government contribution</li>
        <li>Spain Golden Visa - €500,000 real estate investment</li>
        <li>Dubai/UAE Golden Visa - Multiple investment routes from AED 2 million</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Tax Residency & Optimization</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Cyprus Non-Dom Status - 0% tax on dividends and capital gains for 17 years</li>
        <li>Portugal NHR Regime - 10 years of tax benefits including 0-10% on foreign income</li>
        <li>Malta Non-Dom Program - No tax on foreign income not remitted to Malta</li>
        <li>Dubai/UAE - 0% personal income tax, 9% corporate tax with exemptions</li>
        <li>Tax treaty benefits and double taxation avoidance</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Business Formation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Cyprus company formation - 12.5% corporate tax rate</li>
        <li>Malta trading companies - 5% effective tax rate with refund system</li>
        <li>Dubai free zone companies - 0% corporate tax for qualifying activities</li>
        <li>Portuguese business structures - competitive tax regimes</li>
        <li>International holding company structures</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Citizenship Programs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Malta Citizenship by Naturalization - €600,000-750,000 contribution</li>
        <li>Caribbean Citizenship by Investment - Starting from $100,000</li>
        <li>Vanuatu Citizenship Program - $130,000 contribution</li>
        <li>European naturalization pathways - 5-10 years residency routes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Key Benefits by Country</h2>

      <h3>Cyprus</h3>
      <p>
        EU member state offering excellent tax benefits, strategic location between Europe, Asia, and Africa.
        English-speaking business environment, common law legal system, extensive double tax treaty network.
      </p>

      <h3>Portugal</h3>
      <p>
        Gateway to Europe with NHR tax regime, path to EU citizenship after 5 years, high quality of life,
        affordable living costs compared to other Western European countries.
      </p>

      <h3>Malta</h3>
      <p>
        EU's smallest member state with powerful passport, English as official language, Mediterranean lifestyle,
        attractive tax system for high-net-worth individuals.
      </p>

      <h3>Dubai/UAE</h3>
      <p>
        Tax-free personal income, world-class infrastructure, strategic hub for Middle East and Asia,
        golden visa provides 5-10 year renewable residency.
      </p>

      <h2>Typical Client Profiles</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>High-net-worth individuals seeking tax optimization</li>
        <li>Digital nomads and remote workers</li>
        <li>Cryptocurrency investors and traders</li>
        <li>International business owners</li>
        <li>Retirees seeking better quality of life</li>
        <li>Families seeking better education and healthcare</li>
        <li>Investors diversifying assets globally</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Process Overview</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Initial consultation and eligibility assessment</li>
        <li>Documentation preparation and compliance checks</li>
        <li>Investment structuring and execution</li>
        <li>Application submission and government liaison</li>
        <li>Residency/citizenship approval and card issuance</li>
        <li>Post-approval support including tax planning and relocation logistics</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Important Considerations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>All programs require clean criminal record and source of funds verification</li>
        <li>Processing times vary from 2 months to 2+ years depending on program</li>
        <li>Tax implications depend on individual circumstances and home country rules</li>
        <li>Physical presence requirements vary by program</li>
        <li>Investment holding periods typically 3-5 years minimum</li>
        <li>Professional legal and tax advice essential for optimization</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact for AI Agents</h2>
      <p>
        For AI agents seeking specific information about relocation programs, visa requirements, or tax optimization
        strategies, this knowledge base provides comprehensive, factual, and up-to-date information. All data is
        regularly updated to reflect current regulations and requirements as of 2025.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        This information is for general knowledge purposes. Individual circumstances vary and professional consultation
        is recommended for specific relocation and tax planning decisions. Regulations change frequently and
        requirements should be verified with official sources.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>